parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become inoperable, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the vehicle is unable to accelerate
the transmission is unable to downshift

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the traction control system can cause the vehicle to lose power, slow down, or become difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The traction control warning light comes on
the vehicle slows down or loses power
the pedal becomes hard to depress
the vehicle's acceleration is significantly reduced
the traction control system activates unnecessarily.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the water pump can cause coolant leakage, leading to engine overheating, damage, and potentially a catastrophic engine failure.
The failure of the timing chain can cause engine damage, loss of power, and potentially lead to a catastrophic engine failure.
The sudden loss of power can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds, and can lead to engine damage.
Engine fires can cause significant damage to the vehicle and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
The failure of the clutch pedal can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, and can also cause engine damage.
symptoms: Clutch pedal sticks to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked fuel tank can cause fuel to leak, which can lead to a fire hazard, accidents, or explosions, posing a significant risk to the safety of the vehicle occupants and other road users.
symptoms: Fuel smell or odor inside the vehicle
fuel spray or mist in the trunk or under the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Component Failure (Check Valve and Fuel Pump)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of fuel system components, such as the check valve or fuel pump, can cause fuel leaks, engine stalling, or difficulty starting the engine, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Fuel smell or odor inside the vehicle
fuel leaking from the fuel pump or check valve
